parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag inflator can cause the airbag to deploy improperly or not at all, which can lead to serious injury or death in the event of a crash.
symptoms: The airbag warning light illuminates
the airbag does not deploy properly
the airbag cover is pushed up above the dashboard
the airbag inflator is defective.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The delay or unavailability of repair parts can leave vehicles with defective airbag inflators on the road, posing a risk to driver and passenger safety.
symptoms: The dealer or manufacturer is unable to provide repair parts
the repair is delayed or cannot be completed
the contact is unable to have the vehicle repaired.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The manufacturer's inadequate response to the recall can lead to frustration and a lack of trust among vehicle owners, potentially causing them to delay or avoid having the necessary repairs made.
symptoms: The manufacturer is unresponsive or unhelpful
the contact is unable to get a resolution to the issue
the manufacturer is unwilling to provide alternative transportation or a buyback.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ECM can cause the vehicle to stall, shift harshly, or lose power, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The check engine warning light illuminates
the vehicle stalls
the vehicle shifts harshly
the vehicle loses power
the vehicle vibrates abnormally.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unavailability of parts for recall repairs can cause delays and leave vehicles unrepaired, potentially leading to accidents or safety risks.
symptoms: The part to do the recall repair is unavailable
the manufacturer has exceeded a reasonable amount of time for the recall repair.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to stall, shift harshly, or lose power, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls
the vehicle shifts harshly
the vehicle loses power
the transmission fails.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the heat shield can cause the vehicle to vibrate abnormally, which can lead to accidents or safety risks.
symptoms: The vehicle vibrates abnormally
the heat shield is corroded and fractured.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Sudden unintended acceleration can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and potentially lead to serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle suddenly accelerates without warning
often at low speeds
and may continue to accelerate even when the brakes are applied. In some cases
the vehicle may surge forward or jerk violently.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Faulty Accelerator Pedal or Throttle Control
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A faulty accelerator pedal or throttle control can cause sudden unintended acceleration, leading to loss of vehicle control and potentially serious accidents.
symptoms: The accelerator pedal may feel too sensitive
causing sudden starts or jerky movements. The vehicle may surge forward or accelerate unexpectedly
even when the brakes are applied.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Brake Pedal or Hydraulic System Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the brake pedal or hydraulic system can cause the vehicle to accelerate unexpectedly, leading to loss of control and potentially serious accidents.
symptoms: The brake pedal may feel soft or spongy
or the vehicle may surge forward when the brakes are applied. In some cases
the vehicle may not respond to brake input
leading to a loss of control.
